1999-12-14 Tuesday 23:52  tobi

	* date2bin.c (1.4, smapi-1_6_4b-release, smapi-1_6_4a-release): -
	Fixed serious  Y2K bug in the SMAPI. This one affects the SDM part 
	 (Fido *.MSG) of the SMAPI as well as all programs that call  
	ASCII_Date_To_Binary.

1999-12-12 Sunday 08:05  tobi

	* cvtdate.c (1.5): Fixed Y2K bug in the SMAPI. It does not affect
	Squish and Msg, but JAM, and it does affect any program (no matter
	what storage type) that explicitly calls the sc_time routine. The
	bug results in years 2000 ... 2009 being filled in as "0" .. "9"
	instead of "00" .. "09".

1999-12-06 Monday 13:17  tobi

	* makefile.unx (1.9): Re-added generic UNIX makefile

1999-11-30 Tuesday 21:15  sms

