1999-06-27 Sunday 22:26  tobi

	* compiler.h (1.23), fexist.c (1.4), ffind.c (1.6), ffind.h (1.4),
	flush.c (1.3), locking.c (1.10), makefile.ibo (1.6), makefile.wcw
	(1.5), msgapi.h (1.8), structrw.c (1.5): - Bug fix for CSet/2:
	*.MSG was not working (couldn't open Msg Area) - Important bug fix
	for RSXNT and MINGW32 compiler: Binaries created   with those
	compilers completely messed up *.MSG areas.  - Numerous changes to
	the code to make it compile with MINGW32.  - Removed CRs from
	makefile.wcw

1999-06-27 Sunday 22:21  tobi

	* makefile.mgw (1.1): Added makefile.mgw. This makefile is for the
	MingW32 GNU C compiler.  This is a compiler that generates Windows
	95/98/NT binaries. It has two main advantages: First, it creates
	very small executables, because it uses CRTDLL.DLL as its C runtime
	library. Second, "MINGW32 CPD" is a cross compiler edition of this
	compiler that can be used to compile Windows binaries on Unix
	boxes.

1999-06-27 Sunday 14:25  tobi

	* compiler.h (1.22), flush.c (1.2), locking.c (1.9), makefile.ibo
	(1.5), typedefs.h (1.3, smapi-2_2_3-release, smapi-2_2_2-release,
	smapi-2_2_1-release, smapi-2_0_1-release, smapi-2_0_0-release,
	smapi-1_6_4b-release, smapi-1_6_4a-release): Some small changes for
