1998-07-23 Thursday 11:00  tobi

	* locking.c (1.2), makefile.rxw (1.2): Implemented record locking
	for the RSXNT version.

1998-07-23 Thursday 11:00  tobi

	* compiler.h (1.9): Fixed a missing prototype.

1998-07-22 Wednesday 13:54  tobi

	* compiler.h (1.8), locking.c (1.1), makefile.bsd (1.3),
	makefile.emo (1.4), makefile.lnx (1.5), makefile.unx (1.2): Rewrote
	the record locking routines for Unix to use fcntl() instead of
	flock() because fcntl() is more portable and also supports file
	locking via NFS-mounted volumes. Tested on AIX and OSF only, I hope
	this does not break the Linux version. :-). In case of problems:
	e-mail tobi@bland.fido.de

1998-07-16 Thursday 09:02  tobi

	* compiler.h (1.7): Small change for AIX 3.2

1998-07-10 Friday 17:41  tobi

	* compiler.h (1.6): Quick hack to allow the SMAPI to compile on
	Non-BSD systems. This partially removes some of the locking
	mechanisms previously introduced. I will fix it rightly later on.

1998-07-09 Thursday 22:52  tobi

	* compiler.h (1.5), msgapi.h (1.4): Introduced locking mechanism
	with flock on Unix. Changed the locking mode to "blocking", which
	means that the program will simply stop until the area it wants to
	use is released. This is a dirty hack, but as 99% of
	MSGAPI-programs do not check for any return codes, it seems to be
	the only safe way to do it.

1998-07-09 Thursday 22:48  tobi

	* structrw.c (1.2): Fixed a bug in structrw.c that could lead to
	message base corruption under certain circumstances (especially on
	small areas).

1998-07-06 Monday 09:20  tobi

	* compiler.h (1.4): Oops ...

1998-06-30 Tuesday 22:25  tobi

	* compiler.h (1.3), makefile.emo (1.3): The UNIX version now uses
	flock() for squish locking. Better than nothing.

1998-06-30 Tuesday 08:10  tobi

	* stamp.h (1.2, smapi-1_5_6): Cosmetic fix to make it compile on
	AIX 3.2

