1998-06-03 Wednesday 20:46  mt

	* msgapi.c (1.4): fixed bug in NumKludges

1998-05-27 Wednesday 22:39  tobi

	* api_sdm.c (1.3), api_sdm.h (1.2, smapi-2_0_0-release,
	smapi-1_6_4b-release, smapi-1_6_4a-release, smapi-1_5_6), api_sq.h
	(1.2, smapi-1_6_4b-release, smapi-1_6_4a-release, smapi-1_5_6),
	compiler.h (1.2), cvtdate.c (1.3, smapi-1_5_6), fexist.c (1.3,
	smapi-1_5_6), ffind.c (1.3), ffind.h (1.2, smapi-1_5_6),
	makefile.bcd (1.2), makefile.bco (1.2), makefile.bsd (1.2),
	makefile.djg (1.2), makefile.emo (1.2), makefile.hco (1.2),
	makefile.ibo (1.2), makefile.lnx (1.3), makefile.qcd (1.2),
	makefile.rxw (1.1), makefile.wcd (1.2), makefile.wco (1.2),
	makefile.wcw (1.2), makefile.wcx (1.2), msgapi.c (1.3), msgapi.h
	(1.3), old_msg.h (1.2, smapi-2_2_3-release, smapi-2_2_2-release,
	smapi-2_2_1-release, smapi-2_0_1-release, smapi-2_0_0-release,
	smapi-1_6_4b-release, smapi-1_6_4a-release, smapi-1_5_6),
	readme.txt (1.2), structrw.c (1.1): Changes done on 05/28/98 by
	Tobias Ernst:
	
	  - Removed all structure-packing and endianness dependencies. The
	new
	    portable I/O routines are collected in structrw.c. We could now
	    totally leave out the whole #pragma pack stuff if we want, and
	the
	    SMAPI should work on big endian and even more exotic machines.
	
	  - Ported the SMAPI to GNU C for Windows NT using RSXNT/EMX.
	Because
	    I had to use a Win32 API called FindClose, I had to rename the
	    SMAPI-internal routines FindOpen, FindNext and FindClose to
	    FFindOpen, FFindNext and FFindClose.

